Sea Snake Hatchlings are the poisonous offspring of the Sea snake. Their poison damage starts at 50 life points. They require no Slayer level to attack. They give 50 Slayer experience per kill if assigned as a slayer task. They fight with ranged and are weak to slashing weapons. They are found in Miscellania and Etceteria Dungeon, and can be assigned as a task by Vannaka and possibly other Slayer Masters. Snakes are nearest the Etceteria dungeon entrance. If coming from Miscellania dungeon entrance and after using the lift, bring a plank which respawns at the top of the lift. The plank is needed to get across the 3 slippery rocks to avoid 80 life points for each rock.

Strengths and weaknesses[edit | edit source]

Other than antipoison protection, there is nothing special required needed to kill the snakes. Just bring your preferred melee armour and a good slashing weapon(s). These small snakes are not aggressive.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 23 October 2017 (Update):
    • The walk animations for sea snake hatchlings and sea snake young have been updated and smoothed out.
  • patch 17 November 2009 (Update):
    • Fixed a problem with sea snakes and poison attacks.
  • update 22 May 2006 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The examine text is a reference to the Metal Gear video game series in which the title character's name is shouted as such by their commanding officer every time they die.
